quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,37,"Or have you a Book wherein you learn,"
  68,38,"That you shall therein have all that you choose?"
  68,39,"Or have you oaths from Us, reaching to the Day of Resurrection, that yours will be what you judge?"
  69,34,"And urged not on the feeding of Al-Miskîn (the poor).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.34)
  69,35,"So no friend has he here this Day,"
  69,36,"Nor any food except filth from the washing of wounds."
  70,28,"Verily, the torment of their Lord is that before which none can feel secure. -"
  70,29,"And those who guard their chastity (i.e. private parts from illegal sexual acts).{1}",footnotes:1:(V.29) Narrated Sahl bin Sa‘d رضي الله عنه: Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "Whoever can guarantee (the chastity of) what is between his two jaw-bones and what is between his two legs (i.e. his mouth, tongue and his private parts),* I guarantee Paradise for him." (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol. 8, Hadith No.481).
  70,30,"Except from their wives or the (women slaves) whom their right hands possess - for (then) they are not blameworthy."
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned, then were made to enter the Fire. And they found none to help them instead of Allâh."
  71,26,"And Nûh (Noah) said: "
  71,27,""
  72,22,"Say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  72,23,"",footnotes:1:(V.23) See the footnote of (3:85).
  72,24,"Till, when they see that which they are promised, then they will know who it is that is weaker concerning helpers and less important concerning numbers."
  73,16,"But Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) disobeyed the Messenger [Mûsâ (Moses)]; so We seized him with a severe punishment."
  73,17,"Then how can you avoid the punishment, if you disbelieve, on a Day (i.e. the Day of Resurrection) that will make the children grey-headed?"
  73,18,"Whereon the heaven will be cleft asunder? His Promise is certainly to be accomplished."
  74,13,"And children to be by his side."
  74,14,"And made life smooth and comfortable for him."
  74,15,"After all that he desires that I should give more;"
  75,10,"On that Day man will say: "
  75,11,"No! There is no refuge!"
  75,12,"Unto your Lord (Alone) will be the place of rest that Day."
  76,4,"Verily, We have prepared for the disbelievers iron chains, iron collars, and a blazing Fire."
  76,5,"Verily,, the Abrâr (the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism), shall drink of a cup (of wine) mixed with (water from a spring in Paradise called) Kâfûr"
  76,6,"A spring wherefrom the slaves of Allâh will drink, causing it to gush forth abundantly."
  77,1,"By the winds (or angels or the Messengers of Allâh) sent forth one after another."
  77,2,"And by the winds that blow violently."
  77,3,"And by the winds that scatter clouds and rain."